reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice covers
reviews.reviewText: I bought these slip covers for my sofa and loveseat. They look more like suede than leather but they are very nice. They have a great stretchy, super soft feel and stay smooth even after my grandsons sit on them. They're easy to wipe clean with a damp cloth. That's important to me because I have a cat that sheds and kids who like to snack while watching TV. They are made with VERY heavy material and came out of my washer and dryer as good as new. I washed them before putting them on my furniture. The cushion covers are so much better than you get with other slip covers because they encase the entire cushion and have a zipper on them. I would buy another set if they came in different colors. They are absolutely worth the money! If you're ok with the dark brown color you will love these slip covers!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Just wish it was darker and thicker, but it’s nice
reviews.reviewText: We’ve had this less than a week so I can’t speak yet on how it is holding up, but so far we think it looks pretty good. It fits nicely but I wish it was a tad tighter. The reason it has four stars is just because I feel the color is lighter than the picture and it’s a very thin material. I believe the title says “Ultimate leather” so I figured it would be a thicker material. So we shall see how it holds up. I just don’t love the color and how it looks in our gym vs if it were a darker gray. I might return it. But I’m still deciding if we like it. But it still gets 4 stars!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Met my expectations--attractive and soft to the touch
reviews.reviewText: Addressing those reviews who thought it looked either cheap or not like leather or similar critique...Have your expectations in line before you select this item. This is a STRETCH slipcover, which has its main advantage in that it fits the broadest variety of shapes and sizes and still keeps its clean lines. It is never going to look like real or bonded leather--it must be fabric to stretch! That said I really like he leather-look embossing to the fabric, and the texture is very smooth to the touch but has he variation of a leathery item. It's clearly fabric to the eye but looks differently textured enough to please the eye in contrast with other furniture. Just my personal opinion.Otherwise, this performs much the same as my other SureFit stretch covers. I would say it has a LITTLE less give than stretch velvet or others because it is that unique leathery fabric, but still had plenty of give to fit onto my oversized ottoman.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SureFit doesn't disappoint
reviews.reviewText: I've ordered many SureFit covers for my furniture. Well 2023 is the year for a big Apt. overhaul so naturally I wanted something that wouldn't be as cat hair friendly as my previous Cover. This fits the bill. It looks like leather, the color is perfect and doesn't collect cat hair as much. I do wish it were a bit thicker, especially for this price point. But it's really well made and it fit my three seat Sofa perfectly. I would definitely recommend Sure Fit Covers.
